### Akeeba Panopticon API — Self-update
###
### Super-user only. Calls touch the local filesystem under APATH_ROOT and may replace
### running PHP files. DO NOT run against production without a fresh backup. The
### intended call order is: info -> download -> install -> postinstall.

@hostname = https://panopticon.local
@token    = REPLACE-ME-WITH-A-REAL-TOKEN

### 1. Get the current self-update status (no side effects unless ?force=1)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/selfupdate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 1b. Force-bust the update cache and re-check
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/selfupdate?force=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 2. Download the latest update package into the local staging area
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/selfupdate/download
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 3. Install the staged package (extract + OPcache invalidate + clear templates)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/selfupdate/install
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 4. Run the post-install bookkeeping (DB schema, default tasks, cleanup)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/selfupdate/postinstall
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json
